# Human-Readable Code
- ALWAYS use extremely explicit, clearly named variables so that any human developer can easily read and understand the code.
- Avoid using vague, 1-letter, or overly abbreviated variable names.
- Ensure your variable names explain what the data holds or what the function does without needing extensive comments.

# Reusability
- BEFORE writing a new function or component, ALWAYS check the codebase for existing duplicates or similar logic/components. 
- You MUST reuse existing functions and components whenever possible instead of creating new ones.
